  "prompt": "Should I hire a professional to come up with my app name and logo?",
  "response": "Here are some considerations:\n\nPros of hiring a professional:\n1. Expertise in design and branding\n2. Objective perspective\n3. Professional-looking results\n4. Strategic naming that considers marketing\n5. Potential trademark research\n\nCons/Alternatives:\n1. Can be expensive ($500-$5000)\n2. You can do initial brainstorming yourself\n3. Crowdsourcing platforms like 99designs are cheaper\n4. Free logo makers like Canva exist\n5. Freelance designers on platforms like Fiverr are more affordable\n\nRecommendation:\n- For startup/small budget: DIY or affordable freelance options\n- For serious business/funding: Professional branding might be worthwhile\n- Consider your budget and how critical the brand is to your success\n\nTips if doing it yourself:\n- Research competitor names/logos\n- Get feedback from potential users\n- Ensure name is memorable and easy to spell\n- Check trademark availability\n- Test logo legibility at different sizes",
